    • Constructor Detail

      • Mp4MediaChunk

        public Mp4MediaChunk(DataSource dataSource,
             DataSpec dataSpec,
             Format format,
             int trigger,
             long startTimeUs,
             long endTimeUs,
             int nextChunkIndex,
             FragmentedMp4Extractor extractor,
             boolean maybeSelfContained,
             long sampleOffsetUs)
        Parameters:
        dataSource - A DataSource for loading the data.
        dataSpec - Defines the data to be loaded.
        format - The format of the stream to which this chunk belongs.
        trigger - The reason for this chunk being selected.
        startTimeUs - The start time of the media contained by the chunk, in microseconds.
        endTimeUs - The end time of the media contained by the chunk, in microseconds.
        nextChunkIndex - The index of the next chunk, or -1 if this is the last chunk.
        extractor - The extractor that will be used to extract the samples.
        maybeSelfContained - Set to true if this chunk might be self contained, meaning it might contain a moov atom defining the media format of the chunk. This parameter can always be safely set to true. Setting to false where the chunk is known to not be self contained may improve startup latency.
        sampleOffsetUs - An offset to subtract from the sample timestamps parsed by the extractor.

        public boolean seekTo(long positionUs,
             boolean allowNoop)
        Description copied from class: MediaChunk
        Seeks to the specified position within the chunk.
        Specified by:
        seekTo in class MediaChunk
        Parameters:
        positionUs - The desired seek time in microseconds.
        allowNoop - True if the seek is allowed to do nothing if the result is more accurate than seeking to a key frame. Always pass false if it is required that the next sample be a key frame.
        Returns:
        True if the seek results in a discontinuity in the sequence of samples returned by MediaChunk.read(SampleHolder). False otherwise.

      • prepare

        public boolean prepare()
                throws ParserException
        Description copied from class: MediaChunk
        Prepares the chunk for reading. Does nothing if the chunk is already prepared.

        Preparation may require consuming some of the chunk. If the data is not yet available then this method will return false rather than block. The method can be called repeatedly until the return value indicates success.

        Specified by:
        prepare in class MediaChunk
        Returns:
        True if the chunk was prepared. False otherwise.
        Throws:
        ParserException - If an error occurs parsing the media data.
